{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Between 2015 and 2020, the UK Home Office deployed an automated system to support visa decision-making.",
    "The so-called \"visa streaming\" tool classified applicants based on three risk levels, considering nationality as a factor.",
    "Based on the risk assessment, applicants would be subject to more or less scrutiny by public officers.",
    "The practice remained unknown until 2020 when the Joint Council for the Welfare of Immigrants (JCWI) and the law firm \"FoxGlove\" challenged the use of the tool because of its discriminatory effects and lack of transparency.",
    "1 The two civil society organizations argued that the visa streaming algorithm was discriminatory by design: applicants from nationalities identified as suspect nationalities received a higher risk score and, thereby, a higher level of scrutiny by officers."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
